  "local_port": 43674,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the various non-tech companies that visit N.S.I.T for placements and what is the skill set that they are looking for in a person?",
  "response": "Netaji Subhas Institute of Technology (NSIT), now known as Netaji Subhas University of Technology (NSUT), is a prestigious institution in India that attracts a wide range of companies during its placement season. While many tech companies visit the campus, there are also several non-tech companies that participate in the placement process. Here\u2019s a list of some non-tech companies that have visited NSUT, along with the skill sets they typically look for in candidates:\n\n### Non-Tech Companies Visiting NSUT:\n\n1. **McKinsey & Company**\n   - **Industry:** Management Consulting\n   - **Skill Set:** Strong analytical skills, problem-solving abilities, communication skills, leadership potential, and an understanding of business fundamentals.\n\n2. **Bain & Company**\n   - **Industry:** Management Consulting\n   - **Skill Set:** Quantitative skills, critical thinking, teamwork, presentation skills, and a keen interest in business strategy.\n\n3. **Boston Consulting Group (BCG)**\n   - **Industry:** Management Consulting\n   - **Skill Set:** Analytical thinking, problem-solving, leadership skills, ability to work in teams, and strong communication abilities.\n\n4. **Goldman Sachs**\n   - **Industry:** Finance\n   - **Skill Set:** Financial analysis, quantitative skills, problem-solving, attention to detail, and strong communication skills.\n\n5. **J.P. Morgan**\n   - **Industry:** Finance\n   - **Skill Set:** Financial modeling, analytical skills, teamwork, and proficiency in financial software/tools.\n\n6. **Deloitte**\n   - **Industry:** Professional Services (Consulting, Audit, Tax, etc.)\n   - **Skill Set:** Analytical skills, business acumen, communication skills, teamwork, and knowledge of financial principles.\n\n7. **EY (Ernst & Young)**\n   - **Industry:** Professional Services (Consulting, Audit, Tax, etc.)\n   - **Skill Set:** Strong analytical skills, business knowledge, communication skills, teamwork, and understanding of financial and auditing principles.\n\n8. **PwC (PricewaterhouseCoopers)**\n   - **Industry:** Professional Services (Consulting, Audit, Tax, etc.)\n   - **Skill Set:** Analytical skills, business understanding, communication skills, teamwork, and knowledge of financial and auditing principles.\n\n9. **American Express**\n   - **Industry:** Financial Services\n   - **Skill Set:** Financial analysis, customer service orientation, communication skills, and problem-solving abilities.\n\n10. **Procter & Gamble**\n    - **Industry:** Consumer Goods\n    - **Skill Set:** Analytical skills, leadership potential, communication skills, and a strong understanding of business and marketing principles.\n\n### General Skill Sets for Non-Tech Companies:\n\n- **Analytical and Quantitative Skills:** Ability to analyze data and derive insights.\n- **Problem-Solving Abilities:** Creative and logical approach to solving complex issues.\n- **Communication Skills:** Articulate and effective communication, both written and verbal.\n- **Teamwork and Leadership:** Ability to work well in teams and show leadership potential.\n- **Business Acumen:** Understanding of business principles and how they apply to various industries.\n- **Attention to Detail:** Meticulousness and thoroughness in work.\n- **Adaptability:** Ability to quickly learn and adapt to new environments and challenges.\n\nThese are general guidelines, and specific requirements may vary based on the role and company. It's always beneficial for students to tailor their preparation based on the specific job description and company culture.",
